---
description: Documentation-driven change rules for Mesa project organization
alwaysApply: true
---

Read before making changes:

1. Root [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) — tech stack, safety, tenant isolation, commands
2. [`AI_RULES.md`](../../AI_RULES.md) — change workflow and documentation map
3. Relevant docs under `docs/product/`, `docs/design/`, `docs/technical/`, `docs/decisions/`
4. [`docs/ai-schema.md`](../../docs/ai-schema.md) for database context (not full migrations scan)
5. [`docs/optimization.md`](../../docs/optimization.md) when executing project cleanup phases

## Mandatory workflow

1. **Read** related docs and targeted code only — no whole-repo scans
2. **Plan** — output impact scope and approach before editing non-trivial logic
3. **Scope** — no out-of-scope features, no unrelated files, no silent rewrites, no temporary patches
4. **Sync docs** — business rule changes must update `docs/product/` or `docs/technical/`
5. **Verify** — report lint/build/test results after code changes (see `AGENTS.md`)

## Documentation map

| Need | Path |
|------|------|
| Feature boundaries | `docs/product/02-feature-map.md` |
| User flows & rules | `docs/product/03-user-flows.md`, `04-business-rules.md` |
| UI conventions | `docs/design/` |
| Architecture & API | `docs/technical/` |
| ADRs | `docs/decisions/` |

## High-risk areas (require explicit user approval)

Checkout/payment, bill splits, table session lifecycle, print jobs & RLS, migrations, order/kitchen void flows.

Do not expose table UUIDs on receipts — use `display_name` only.

## Optimization phases

Execute one phase from `docs/optimization.md` at a time; stop for user confirmation before the next phase.
